From d6955eb6738fb39e86d0129ac8d25fb527d7e0b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tcfialho <tcfialho@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 01:06:17 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 4/7] maindeck anim Step 2b: scale pop on open/close (around
 center)

Open pops 0.65->1, close shrinks 1->0.65, alongside the existing fade. Scale is
applied via SceneBuffer.setDestSize around the window center; the tree node is
shifted by (1-f)*size/2 to recenter, so borders/popups ride along.

Avoids the compounding trap (reading the buffer's already-scaled dest size each
tick): dest size is always computed from the STABLE natural box, never from the
current dest. Single-buffer (tiled) windows scale; multi-buffer windows with
subsurfaces degrade gracefully to fade-only (no per-buffer position machine).
On finish, applyScale(1.0) restores natural size so nothing stays scaled.

Close orphans carry their origin + natural size to scale around center too.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
